<task id="WKSP-010" project="spaarke-workspace-user-configuration-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Fix useFeedTodoSync to return no-op stubs when provider is missing</title>
    <phase>2</phase>
    <tags>shared-components, bugfix</tags>
    <estimated-effort>2h</estimated-effort>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <dependencies>WKSP-001</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    <role>Senior TypeScript/C# developer implementing workspace personalization</role>
    <goal>Fix the useFeedTodoSync hook to return safe no-op stubs when FeedTodoSyncProvider is absent, instead of throwing an error. This enables SmartToDo to work independently outside the provider tree.</goal>
    <context>
      Currently, useFeedTodoSync() throws an error if called outside FeedTodoSyncProvider. This was
      intentional for the original LegalWorkspace where both ActivityFeed and SmartToDo are always
      rendered together inside the provider.

      With the Section Registry, SmartToDo can now be placed in a workspace layout without ActivityFeed.
      In that scenario, there is no FeedTodoSyncProvider in the tree, and useFeedTodoSync throws,
      crashing the entire workspace.

      The fix: when context is null (no provider), return a NOOP_SYNC constant that satisfies the
      IFeedTodoSyncContextValue interface with safe defaults:
      - isFlagged() returns false
      - toggleFlag() returns resolved Promise
      - getFlaggedCount() returns 0
      - isPending() returns false
      - getError() returns undefined
      - subscribe() returns a no-op unsubscribe function
      - initFlags() is a no-op
      - _flagsSnapshot is an empty ReadonlyMap

      This is a critical behavioral change — SmartToDo's flag sync features silently degrade rather than crash.
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - MUST NOT break existing behavior when FeedTodoSyncProvider IS present — all current consumers must work identically
      - MUST return a stable singleton NOOP_SYNC object (not recreated on each call) to avoid unnecessary re-renders
      - MUST add a console.debug() warning when falling back to no-op, so developers notice the missing provider during development
      - MUST NOT change the IFeedTodoSyncContextValue interface
      - MUST NOT modify FeedTodoSyncContext.tsx or the provider implementation
      - The NOOP_SYNC constant MUST satisfy the full IFeedTodoSyncContextValue interface
      - toggleFlag MUST return Promise.resolve() (not throw)
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/workspaceConfig.tsx</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/hooks/useFeedTodoSync.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/contexts/FeedTodoSyncContext.tsx</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/hooks/useFeedTodoSync.ts</file>
    <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/contexts/FeedTodoSyncContext.tsx</file>
    <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/SmartToDo/SmartToDo.tsx</file>
    <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/hooks/useTodoItems.ts</file>
  </relevant-files>
  <steps>
    <step id="1">Read useFeedTodoSync.ts and FeedTodoSyncContext.tsx to fully understand the IFeedTodoSyncContextValue interface and all its method signatures.</step>
    <step id="2">Define a NOOP_SYNC constant in useFeedTodoSync.ts that implements IFeedTodoSyncContextValue with safe no-op stubs: isFlagged returns false, toggleFlag returns Promise.resolve(), getFlaggedCount returns 0, isPending returns false, getError returns undefined, subscribe returns () => {}, initFlags is () => {}, _flagsSnapshot is new Map().</step>
    <step id="3">Modify the useFeedTodoSync function: replace the throw statement with a console.debug warning and return NOOP_SYNC when ctx is null.</step>
    <step id="4">Verify that the NOOP_SYNC object is module-level (singleton) so it does not cause referential inequality on re-renders.</step>
    <step id="5">Check all consumers of useFeedTodoSync (search for imports) to confirm none rely on the throw behavior for error boundary detection.</step>
    <step id="6">Verify TypeScript compilation succeeds and the hook's return type is still IFeedTodoSyncContextValue.</step>
    <step id="7">Export the NOOP_SYNC constant for testing purposes (named export, secondary to the hook default).</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>useFeedTodoSync returns NOOP_SYNC (not throws) when FeedTodoSyncProvider is absent from the component tree</criterion>
    <criterion>NOOP_SYNC satisfies the complete IFeedTodoSyncContextValue interface with all 8 members</criterion>
    <criterion>NOOP_SYNC is a stable module-level singleton (same reference on every call)</criterion>
    <criterion>A console.debug message is logged when falling back to NOOP_SYNC</criterion>
    <criterion>Existing behavior is unchanged when FeedTodoSyncProvider IS in the tree</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
